---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import InteriorPage from "../../components/InteriorPage.astro";
import Instructors from '../../components/instructors/Instructors.astro';
import Instructor from '../../components/instructors/Instructor.astro';
import { SITE_SEO } from '../../config/site';
import type { ImageMetadata } from 'astro';

const instructorImageModules = import.meta.glob<{ default: ImageMetadata }>(
  '/src/assets/images/instructors/*.{avif,webp,png,jpg,jpeg}',
  { eager: true }
);

const instructorImages = Object.fromEntries(
  Object.entries(instructorImageModules).map(([path, module]) => [
    path.split('/').pop()!,
    module.default,
  ])
);

---

<Layout title={`Meet our Instructors | ${SITE_SEO.name.long}`} description={SITE_SEO.description}>
	<InteriorPage 
    heading="Meet our Instructors" 
    lead="Meet our dedicated instructors who bring a wealth of knowledge and experience to our dojo. Each instructor is committed to helping students of all ages and skill levels achieve their martial arts goals."
  >
    <hr />
    <Instructors>
      <Instructor 
        id="kyoshi-fred-sypher"
        featured={true}
        name="Fred Sypher"
        title="Kyoshi"
        img={instructorImages['kyoshi-fred-sypher.avif']}
        imgAspectRatio="4 / 3"
      >
        <p>I was drafted in 1965 and joined the US Air Force. While stationed at Fort Myer, Virginia in 1966, I discovered Okinawan Kenpo under Gary Saluter, a fourth-degree black belt who had trained under Nakamura Sensei on Okinawa. After a flood destroyed Saluter's dojo, I was stationed on Okinawa in October 1967, where I trained in Shorinjiryu under Kise Fusei on Kadena Air Base. Sensei Kise was then a student of tenth-degree grand master Hohan Soken.</p>
        <p>In spring 1968, Sensei Kise announced he would now teach Shorinryu Matsumura Seito, which he had been studying under Master Soken. I devoted every available hour to this system until my discharge in March 1970, returning to Maryland as a third-degree black belt. I became lead instructor of the Patuxent River Karate Club, then in 1974 opened the Isshokan Karate Dojo in Lexington Park—the first commercial karate school in St. Mary's County. I also taught Maryland's first accredited high school karate class at Ryken High School in Leonardtown. After receiving my fifth-degree black belt in 1977, I closed the dojo to marry and attend college.</p>
        <p>For over 50 years, I have studied and taught exclusively Shorinryu Matsumura Seito. I live in Westminster, Maryland and conduct monthly seminars at Dean's Okinawan Martial Arts and Self Defense School in Hollywood, Maryland. I greatly enjoy sharing what I've learned over five decades of devoted practice. Learn more information about <a href="https://SMOKA-USA.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Shorin-Ryu Matsumura Orthodox (SEITO) Karate Association</a> on James Coffman’s web site.</p>
      </Instructor>
      <Instructor 
        id="kyoshi-wayne-dean"
        name="Wayne Dean"
        rank="Hachi-Dan"
        title="Kyoshi"
        img={instructorImages['kyoshi-wayne-dean.avif']}
        imgAspectRatio="3 / 4"
      >
        <p>Sensei Wayne Dean holds an 8th degree black belt and has been studying Shorin Ryu Matsumura Orthodox Karate since 1971. His instructor, Sensei Fred Sypher, was a student of Fusei Kise and Master Hohan Soken while stationed in Okinawa. Since September 2002 Sensei Dean has operated his own Karate Dojo located in Hollywood Maryland offering both children and adult classes in Karate, Kobudo, and Self Defense.</p>
      </Instructor>
      <Instructor 
        id="senpai-kirk-dean"
        name="Kirk Dean"
        title="Senpai"
        img={instructorImages['kirk-dean.avif']}
        imgAspectRatio="3 / 4"
      >
        <p>Kirk Dean began his training in 1993 with Sensei Dean and Mark Gillingham when they taught with the Park and Recreation Center.  He has also studied Shorin –Ryu Matsumura Seito with Sensei Dan Buckner and Sensei Fred Sypher. He is the senior instructor under Sensei Dean.</p>
      </Instructor>
      <Instructor 
        id="senpai-phillip-dean"
        name="Phillip Dean"
        title="Senpai"
        img={instructorImages['phillip-dean.avif']}
        imgAspectRatio="3 / 4"
      >
        <p>Philip Dean has been studying Shorin- Ryu Matsumura Seito karate with Sensei Wayne Dean since 2002.  He has also studied with Sensei Fred Sypher when Sensei Sypher is a quest instructor at  the Dojo. Philip also helps Sensei Dean with teaching classes for the Children and Adult’s.</p>
      </Instructor>
      <Instructor 
        id="senpai-chris-schumacher"
        name="Chris Schumacher"
        rank="Ni-Dan"
        title="Senpai"
        img={instructorImages['chris-schumacher.avif']}
        imgAspectRatio="3 / 4"
      >
        <p>Chris Schumacher started studying Shorin Ryu Karate with Sensei Wayne Dean in 2004 after a deployment to Okinawa.  He was recently promoted to Ni-Dan (2nd degree Black belt) in January 2019. He has also studied the Marine Corps Martial Arts Program (MCMAP), Aikido and Krav Maga. Mr. Schumacher is also a 21 year veteran of the US Navy, serving with the US Marine Corps as a Hospital Corpsman. </p>
      </Instructor>
    </Instructors>
  </InteriorPage>
</Layout>
